---
// The three-plane architecture with live-measured per-service RAM.
// Numbers: apps/baas/wiki/cost-analysis.md §1 ("Where the weight is").
---

<figure>
	<svg class="gb-diagram" viewBox="0 0 720 330" role="img" aria-labelledby="dg-planes-title dg-planes-desc">
		<title id="dg-planes-title">The three-plane architecture</title>
		<desc id="dg-planes-desc">
			Three stacked planes. TypeScript orchestration plane: query-router 62.7 MiB, permission-engine 64.7
			MiB, email 46 MiB, log 84 MiB — 46 to 84 MiB per service. Go control plane: adapter-registry 37.9
			MiB, tenant-control 58.6 MiB, webhook-dispatcher 6.8 MiB — 7 to 59 MiB per service. Rust data
			plane, the hot path: data-plane-router 3.3 MiB and realtime 17.8 MiB, serving requests in 8
			milliseconds where the old Node path needed 40.
		</desc>

		<rect class="d-box d-box--ts" x="20" y="16" width="680" height="92" rx="12" />
		<text class="d-title" x="40" y="44">TypeScript — orchestration</text>
		<text class="d-faint" x="680" y="44" text-anchor="end">fast-changing business logic · 46–84 MiB / service</text>
		<rect class="d-chip" x="40" y="60" width="180" height="28" rx="14" />
		<text class="d-label" x="130" y="78" text-anchor="middle">query-router <tspan class="d-ram">62.7 MiB</tspan></text>
		<rect class="d-chip" x="232" y="60" width="212" height="28" rx="14" />
		<text class="d-label" x="338" y="78" text-anchor="middle">permission-engine <tspan class="d-ram">64.7 MiB</tspan></text>
		<rect class="d-chip" x="456" y="60" width="116" height="28" rx="14" />
		<text class="d-label" x="514" y="78" text-anchor="middle">email <tspan class="d-ram">46</tspan></text>
		<rect class="d-chip" x="584" y="60" width="100" height="28" rx="14" />
		<text class="d-label" x="634" y="78" text-anchor="middle">log <tspan class="d-ram">84</tspan></text>

		<rect class="d-box d-box--go" x="20" y="122" width="680" height="92" rx="12" />
		<text class="d-title" x="40" y="150">Go — control plane</text>
		<text class="d-faint" x="680" y="150" text-anchor="end">tenancy · identity · secrets · 7–59 MiB / service</text>
		<rect class="d-chip" x="40" y="166" width="216" height="28" rx="14" />
		<text class="d-label" x="148" y="184" text-anchor="middle">adapter-registry <tspan class="d-ram">37.9 MiB</tspan></text>
		<rect class="d-chip" x="268" y="166" width="196" height="28" rx="14" />
		<text class="d-label" x="366" y="184" text-anchor="middle">tenant-control <tspan class="d-ram">58.6</tspan></text>
		<rect class="d-chip" x="476" y="166" width="208" height="28" rx="14" />
		<text class="d-label" x="580" y="184" text-anchor="middle">webhook-dispatcher <tspan class="d-ram">6.8</tspan></text>

		<rect class="d-box d-box--rust" x="20" y="228" width="680" height="92" rx="12" />
		<text class="d-title" x="40" y="256">Rust — data plane</text>
		<text class="d-faint" x="680" y="256" text-anchor="end">the hot path · 8 ms p50 (was 40 ms in Node)</text>
		<rect class="d-chip d-box--accent" x="40" y="272" width="232" height="28" rx="14" />
		<text class="d-label" x="156" y="290" text-anchor="middle">data-plane-router <tspan class="d-ram d-ram--tiny">3.3 MiB</tspan></text>
		<rect class="d-chip" x="284" y="272" width="172" height="28" rx="14" />
		<text class="d-label" x="370" y="290" text-anchor="middle">realtime <tspan class="d-ram d-ram--tiny">17.8 MiB</tspan></text>
		<text class="d-faint" x="476" y="290">← ABAC + field masks run in-process</text>
	</svg>
	<figcaption class="gb-diagram-note">
		Per-service RAM, measured live (<span class="gb-mono">make bench-footprint</span>, 2026-06-11). The old
		hot path — query-router + permission-engine — was 127 MiB of Node; it is now 3.3 MiB of Rust.
	</figcaption>
</figure>
